author: @XiaodanZhang2
text: The accuracy inconsistent is not from naive bayesian, but from all_words.keys() is random since the keys in a python dictionary is not sorted;  the better way to extract features is to calculate tfidf scores, have them sorted, and then do the training. the result will be consisent

author: @yorickbolster782
text: Really appreciate the videos, but I think this should really be mentioned here as well. As others mentioned in the last video, the instability is because you take the top 3000 of the dictionary, which are different every time. You should call all_word.most_common(3000) to get the top 3000 most common ones, now you get a random selection.
